Refers to the equivalent numeric identifier of the Seniority Code.

Refers to the code related to the seniority level. The standard seniority values are Senior, Mezzanine and Subordinate. Senior refers that the account is senior in receiving any cash flows, and also receives priorities during liquidation. The Mezzanine is applicable only for debt securities, wherein there can be tranches in between the senior and the subordinate. The subordinate refers that the account receives the least priority in the cash flows and also during liquidation, is the last to be paid off.
